## 3. What Business This Is

In plain language:

- **Category** — one line (not five buzzwords)
- **One-liner** — for [customer] who [problem], we [solution]
- **Business model** — usage / marketplace / SaaS / protocol / hybrid
- **Not this** — what you are *not* (kill false categories)

Syra lens: pay-per-call machine money for agents, not “another AI wrapper.”

## 4. Who the Customer Is

Define:

| Layer | Content |
| --- | --- |
| Primary ICP | title, context, urgency |
| Secondary ICP | only if it does not dilute |
| Buyer vs user | who pays vs who integrates |
| Anti-persona | who to ignore for now |
| Jobs to be done | 1–3 sharp jobs |

For marketplaces (Syra): name **both sides** (consumer agents vs providers) and which side to win first.

## 5. What We Should Charge + Pricing

Recommend:

1. **Pricing model** — per call, % take rate, tiers, subscription+overage
2. **Concrete numbers** — starter prices, floors, enterprise path (label as hypotheses if unvalidated)
3. **Packaging** — free tier / paid / provider economics
4. **Why this price** — value metric, willingness, cost floor
5. **What not to charge for** — activation killers

Coordinate with `finance-pricing` for deep margin math; cofounder rule gives the **market-facing** recommendation.

Syra: minimum viable micropayment, take rate vs provider earnings, agent-friendly predictability.

## 6. Marketing

Give a practical plan:

- **Positioning** — category + differentiation
- **Message pillars** — 3 claims with proof from product
- **Channels** — ranked for this ICP (dev/crypto/agent communities)
- **Content** — what to publish weekly
- **Budget** — time-first vs paid (solo founder default: time)

No spray-and-pray. One primary channel until it works.

## 7. Landing Page

Specify structure (not vague “make it pretty”):

1. Hero outcome + primary CTA
2. Who it's for
3. How it works (≤3 steps)
4. Proof (demo, metrics, code snippet)
5. Pricing teaser or “pay per call” clarity
6. FAQ / objections
7. Final CTA → docs/SDK/dashboard

Call out what the current `web/` landing gets wrong if visible. Defer visual craft to `ui-ux-design`.

## 8. SEO

Plan:

- **Primary keywords** — intent-mapped (problem + category)
- **Pages to exist** — home, docs, use cases, comparisons, glossary
- **Technical** — indexable docs, performance, clean URLs
- **Authority** — GitHub, integrations, tutorials
- **What not to do** — keyword stuffing, fake blog spam

Syra examples: x402 API, pay per call API, agent payments, machine money.

## 9. Launch Strategy

Phased:

| Phase | Goal | Tactics |
| --- | --- | --- |
| Pre-launch | waitlist / design partners | 10–20 target users |
| Soft launch | learning | private Discord/X circle |
| Public launch | attention + activation | one narrative, working quickstart |
| Post-launch | retention | support, case study, iterate |

Checklist: product works, docs <5 min, analytics on, support path, status for failures.

## 10. Viral Strategy

Design loops that fit the product (not “make it go viral”):

- **Built-in loops** — referrals, shareable outputs, provider marketplace gravity, agent-to-agent calls
- **Triggered loops** — templates, public badges, “powered by,” OSS examples
- **Incentives** — credits, fee discounts (avoid unsustainable subsidies)
- **K-factor honesty** — what is plausible for this ICP

Syra: agents calling paid endpoints can be distribution if DX and pricing are clear.

## 11. Fundraising Strategy

Only if it serves the business:

- **Raise or not** — when revenue/path is clearer than dilution need
- **Story** — problem, why now, why this team/repo, wedge, market
- **Proof to gather first** — paid usage, retention, provider supply, design partners
- **Round shape** — stage, use of funds (eng, security audit, DevRel — not vanity)
- **Investor profile** — crypto infra, AI agents, developer tools
- **Red flags to fix before** — broken activation, unclear model, multi-product sprawl

If bootstrap is better, say so bluntly.

